      "note_no": "3804",
      "note": "In the Old Testament, 2 Chronicles, Chapters 3, and 4, are described the various costly materials with which Solomon's Temple was built, and it was furnished with vessels, candlesticks, lamps, censers, etc. \"Solomon made all these vessels in great abundance: for the weight of the brass could not be found out\" (2 Chronicles, 4:18). \"Also he made a molten sea often cubits from brim to brim, round in compass, and five cubits the height thereof: and a line of thirty cubits did compass it round about\" (2 Chronicles, 4:2). The receptacle or \"sea\" or Font was made of molten brass: presumably it contained flowing water for washing with."
